  Biography (updated 3/12/2017)



 
Stan
Meresman is a professional independent Director, Audit Committee Chair, advisor
& mentor. He advises CEOs & CFOs on preparing to become a public
reporting company, IPO process, operating as a public company, and scaling the
company for rapid growth. He is a "financial expert� as defined by under
the rules of the SEC. Currently,
Stan is a director of Snap
(SNAP), Palo Alto Networks (PANW), and formerly LinkedIn
(LNKD-prior to acquisition); and private companies Medallia, Saama Technologies and HyTrust.   Previously Stan
was an advisor to management at Pinterest, Dropbox and Nutanix.
 
As a
CFO, Stan has taken a company public (Cypress Semiconductor), served as CFO of
two NYSE-listed companies: Silicon Graphics, Inc. (SGI) and Cypress
Semiconductor. As Chair of the Audit Committee, he has guided five companies
through their successful IPO (Snap, LinkedIn, Zynga, Riverbed Technology,
Polycom).

Currently, Stan is
a Board member of Snap (SNAP),
where he is Chair of
Audit Committee; and Board member of Palo Alto Networks (PANW), where he
is Chair of Audit Committee.
 
Previously, Stan has served
on Boards including LinkedIn
(LNKD), Zynga (ZNGA), Riverbed Technology (RVBD), Polycom (PLCM),
Meru
Networks (MERU) and VMware (as a private company), as well as others. He
had been General Partner and COO of Technology Crossover Ventures (TCV), a private equity and venture capital firm
focused on growth technology companies. 
 
Earlier
in his career, Stan was SVP & CFO of Silicon Graphics (NYSE) where revenue
grew from $250 million to $3.8 billion, completed four acquisitions and a dozen
strategic alliances. Previously, Stan was VP, Finance & Administration
and CFO of Cypress Semiconductor (NYSE) where revenue grew from $2 million to
over $100 million and successfully completed its IPO. 

Stan received his MBA from the Stanford
Graduate School of Business; and B.S. in Industrial Engineering and Operations Research
from the University of California, Berkeley. He has attended Stanford Law
School Directors' College Corporate Governance programs. Stan was a panel
speaker NYSE IPO BOARD FORUM "Building Boards� December 2013.
 
Stan
currently serves as a  Chair of the Board of Trustees of the Sunset
Cultural Center, Carmel. He previously served on the Board of Trustees of the
Palo Alto Medical Foundation Community Board, Carmel Bach Festival Foundation,
and Castilleja School, Palo Alto, and as Chair of the Board of Family Service
Mid-Peninsula, Palo Alto. Stan was past President of the Board of the Financial
Executives Institute (FEI), Silicon Valley Chapter. He was a past President of
the Board of the Monterey Peninsula Country Club, Pebble Beach.





