Executive Profile
Stanley J. Meresman  Strategic Advisor, Trident Capital CybersecurityAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 6 Board Members in 6 different organizations across 19 different industries.See Board Relationships70--
Background

		Mr. Stanley J. Meresman, also known as Stan, is a Strategic Advisor at Trident Capital Cybersecurity. Mr. Meresman served as an Advisor of Silicon Image, Inc. He served as the Chief Financial Officer of Technology Crossover Ventures. He served as an Advisor to Inktomi Corporation. He served as a Venture Partner of Technology Crossover Ventures from January 2004 to December 2004. He joined TCV in November 2001. Mr. Meresman served as a General Partner and Chief Operating ... Officer of Technology Crossover Ventures from November 2001 to December 2003. He served as a Senior Vice President of Finance and Chief Financial Officer at Graphics Properties Holdings, Inc. (formerly, Silicon Graphics, Inc.) from May 1989 to May 1997. Prior to joining Silicon Graphics, he served as a Vice President of Finance and Administration and Chief Financial Officer at Cypress Semiconductor Corporation from 1985 to 1989. Mr. Meresman is the President of the Board of the Financial Executives Institute (FEI), Silicon Valley Chapter. He has been a Director of Snap Inc. since July 2015 and Palo Alto Networks, Inc. since September 20, 2014. He has been a Director of Saama Technologies, Inc. since December 2014 and Medallia, Inc. since July 2015. He serves as a Director of HyTrust, Inc. He served as a Director of LinkedIn Corporation from October 2010 to December 08, 2016. He has over 25 years experience serving in Senior Executive Financial and Operating positions in high growth technology companies. He served as a Director of Aether Software, Inc. and Corefino Services, LLC (formerly, Corefino Inc.). He served as a Director of Zynga, Inc. since June 2011 until June 11, 2015. He served as Director of SPL Worldgroup, Inc. He served as a Director of GoRemote Internet Communications, Inc. He served as a Member of Advisory Board of ITM Software Corp. He served as a Director of Meru Networks, Inc. from September 8, 2010 to May 21, 2013. He served as a Director at Riverbed Technology, Inc. since March 2005 until May 2012. He served as a Director of Alien Technology Corporation since May 2005. He served as a Director of LightSurf Technologies Inc. and Starfish Software, Inc. He served as a Director of Force10 Networks, Inc. He served as a Director of Polycom Inc. from January 1995 to May 30, 2007 and Turn Inc. since May 2014. He served as a Director of Technology Crossover Ventures, 2wire Inc. and VMware, Inc. He is a Guest Lecturer of Stanford Graduate School of Engineering Capital Formation course and for a Harvard Business School management course. He received Stanford Business School's "Entrepreneurial Company of the Year" award. Mr. Meresman holds a BSc Degree in Industrial Engineering and Operations Research from University of California, Berkeley in 1968 and an M.B.A. Degree from Stanford Graduate School of Business in 1972. He attended Stanford Law School Directors' College corporate governance program in June 2010.Read Full Background




